---
import BlogLayout from "@/layouts/BlogLayout.astro";
import DocFrame from "@/components/DocFrame.astro";

const title = "Issue Report Samples";
const description =
  "Manual QA issue report samples for B2B spare part e-commerce with reproducible steps, impact, and validation notes.";

const latexSource = String.raw`
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}

\section*{ISSUE REPORT SAMPLES (SANITIZED)}
\subsection*{Project: B2B Spare Part Marketplace (Indonesia Buyer - China Seller)}
This document shows how critical and high issues are reported in a manual QA workflow so developers can reproduce fast and fix with clear priority.

\subsection*{1. Document Info}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline
Field & Value \\
\hline
Version & 1.1 \\
Owner & Theodore - Software QA Engineer \\
Date & March 2026 \\
Type & Portfolio sample (sanitized, manual QA) \\
Status & Ready for triage review \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{2. Context}
This platform serves Indonesian buyers and China sellers. Order quality risk is high because flow includes currency conversion, invoice checks, shipping handover, and multilingual UI.

\subsection*{3. Reporting Goals}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Every issue is reproducible in less than 10 minutes.
\item 2) Severity and business impact are clear for triage.
\item 3) Evidence is enough for developer analysis without extra ping-pong.
\item 4) Retest notes confirm fix result before release sign-off.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{4. Severity and SLA Guide}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|l|}
\hline
Severity & Business Impact & Response Target & Retest Target \\
\hline
Critical & Payment, order, or shipment cannot proceed & 2 hours & Same day \\
High & Main flow works but with major risk & 1 business day & Next build \\
Medium & Workaround available & 2 business days & Planned cycle \\
Low & Cosmetic or minor copy issue & Backlog & Planned cycle \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{5. Mandatory Report Fields}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Bug ID, title, severity, priority, and environment.
\item 2) Preconditions and exact steps to reproduce.
\item 3) Expected result and actual result.
\item 4) Impact statement (user, business, and operational risk).
\item 5) Evidence (screenshots, logs, payload, and SQL check if needed).
\item 6) Validation notes after fix and retest status.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{6. Critical Sample A}
\subsection*{Title: Checkout Total Mismatch Between Cart and Invoice}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline
Field & Value \\
\hline
Bug ID & BUG-B2B-241 \\
Severity / Priority & Critical / P1 \\
Environment & Staging 2026.03.20, Chrome 134, Buyer ID role \\
Module & Cart, Checkout, Invoice \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{Repro Steps}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Login as buyer and add 3 spare parts from China seller.
\item 2) Apply seller discount and choose express shipping.
\item 3) Continue checkout and open generated invoice page.
\item 4) Compare cart total, checkout total, and invoice total.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Expected Result}
Total amount is consistent on cart, checkout, and invoice.

\subsection*{Actual Result}
Invoice total is higher by IDR 12,500 after discount and shipping recalculation.

\subsection*{Impact}
Buyer sees inconsistent price and cannot trust invoice accuracy. Finance team receives manual correction requests.

\subsection*{Validation Notes}
Fix retested on build 2026.03.21-rc1 with 6 price combinations. Result: Passed.

\subsection*{7. Critical Sample B}
\subsection*{Title: Payment Confirmed but Order Status Stuck at Pending Payment}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline
Field & Value \\
\hline
Bug ID & BUG-B2B-257 \\
Severity / Priority & Critical / P1 \\
Environment & Staging 2026.03.20, Safari 17, Buyer and Seller dashboard \\
Module & Payment Confirmation, Order Status \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{Repro Steps}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Complete order and upload payment proof.
\item 2) Finance verifier marks payment as accepted.
\item 3) Refresh buyer order history and seller order queue.
\item 4) Check status in admin panel.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Expected Result}
All panels change status to Paid and ready for shipment.

\subsection*{Actual Result}
Admin panel shows Paid, but buyer and seller panels remain Pending Payment.

\subsection*{Impact}
Shipment handover is blocked and seller misses dispatch SLA.

\subsection*{Validation Notes}
Retest on build 2026.03.22-rc2 with 5 orders. Status sync works across all panels. Result: Passed.

\subsection*{8. High Sample C}
\subsection*{Title: Indonesian Label on Tax Detail Is Misleading}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|}
\hline
Field & Value \\
\hline
Bug ID & BUG-B2B-266 \\
Severity / Priority & High / P2 \\
Environment & Staging 2026.03.20, Mobile web Chrome Android \\
Module & Checkout Summary, Localization \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{Repro Steps}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Open checkout in Indonesian language.
\item 2) Select product with import tax.
\item 3) Review tax line in order summary.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{Expected Result}
Label clearly explains import tax component.

\subsection*{Actual Result}
Label text implies optional fee, causing confusion in UAT.

\subsection*{Impact}
Buyer misunderstanding increases drop-off at payment step.

\subsection*{Validation Notes}
Copy updated and reviewed by product and legal. Retest passed on 2026.03.23.

\subsection*{9. Defect Outcome Summary}
\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|l|}
\hline
Bug ID & Severity & Fix Status & Retest Result \\
\hline
BUG-B2B-241 & Critical & Resolved & Passed \\
BUG-B2B-257 & Critical & Resolved & Passed \\
BUG-B2B-266 & High & Resolved & Passed \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

\subsection*{10. Impact in Numbers}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Average triage clarification round: 4 to 1 after template standardization.
\item 2) Average developer reproduction time: 35 minutes to 11 minutes.
\item 3) Reopened bug rate: 18 percent to 6 percent.
\item 4) Release blockers resolved before UAT sign-off: 100 percent for this cycle.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{11. QA Best Practices Applied}
\begin{itemize}
\item 1) Report only one core problem per ticket to avoid mixed root cause.
\item 2) Use stable test data and mention exact account role.
\item 3) Attach evidence in sequence: UI, API, DB (if needed).
\item 4) Write impact in business language, not only technical language.
\item 5) Always close with retest notes and tested build version.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{12. Redaction Note}
Simulation shared in compliance with NDA.

\end{document}
`;
---

<BlogLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <header class="w-full max-w-[960px] mx-auto px-6 py-10 flex justify-between items-center">
    <a href="/" class="text-[20px] font-sans font-bold tracking-[-0.04em] text-[var(--foreground-primary)] hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">
      Theodore's <span class="text-[var(--foreground-muted)] font-normal">Portfolio</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/" class="text-[12px] font-sans font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-[var(--foreground-muted)] hover:text-[var(--foreground-primary)] transition-colors">
      ← All Projects
    </a>
  </header>

  <main class="w-full max-w-[960px] mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
    <DocFrame hideHeader={true} plainPage={true}>
      <div id="latex-live-root" class="latex-live-root">
        <p class="latex-loading">Loading document...</p>
      </div>
    </DocFrame>
  </main>

  <script is:inline define:vars={{ latexSource }}>
    (function () {
      var source = (latexSource || "").trim();
      var root = document.getElementById("latex-live-root");

      function decodeLatexText(text) {
        return text
          .replace(/\\&/g, "&")
          .replace(/\\%/g, "%")
          .replace(/\\_/g, "_")
          .replace(/\\#/g, "#")
          .replace(/\\\$/g, "$")
          .replace(/\\\\/g, " ");
      }

      function escapeHtml(text) {
        return text
          .replace(/&/g, "&amp;")
          .replace(/</g, "&lt;")
          .replace(/>/g, "&gt;")
          .replace(/"/g, "&quot;")
          .replace(/'/g, "&#39;");
      }

      function cleanInline(text) {
        return escapeHtml(decodeLatexText(text.trim()));
      }

      function parseSection(line, command) {
        var prefix = "\\" + command + "*{";
        if (!line.startsWith(prefix) || !line.endsWith("}")) return null;
        return line.slice(prefix.length, -1);
      }

      function renderTable(rows) {
        if (!rows.length) return "";
        var header = rows[0];
        var body = rows.slice(1);
        var thead =
          "<thead><tr>" +
          header
            .map(function (cell) {
              return "<th>" + cleanInline(cell) + "</th>";
            })
            .join("") +
          "</tr></thead>";
        var tbody =
          "<tbody>" +
          body
            .map(function (row) {
              return (
                "<tr>" +
                row
                  .map(function (cell) {
                    return "<td>" + cleanInline(cell) + "</td>";
                  })
                  .join("") +
                "</tr>"
              );
            })
            .join("") +
          "</tbody>";
        return '<div class="latex-table-container"><table>' + thead + tbody + "</table></div>";
      }

      function renderLatexSubset(input) {
        var lines = input.split(/\r?\n/);
        var chunks = [];
        var paragraph = [];
        var i = 0;

        function flushParagraph() {
          if (!paragraph.length) return;
          var text = paragraph.join(" ").replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim();
          if (text) chunks.push("<p>" + cleanInline(text) + "</p>");
          paragraph = [];
        }

        while (i < lines.length) {
          var line = lines[i].trim();
          if (
            !line ||
            line.startsWith("\\documentclass") ||
            line === "\\begin{document}" ||
            line === "\\end{document}"
          ) {
            flushParagraph();
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          var sectionTitle = parseSection(line, "section");
          if (sectionTitle !== null) {
            flushParagraph();
            chunks.push("<h2>" + cleanInline(sectionTitle) + "</h2>");
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          var subsectionTitle = parseSection(line, "subsection");
          if (subsectionTitle !== null) {
            flushParagraph();
            chunks.push("<h3>" + cleanInline(subsectionTitle) + "</h3>");
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          if (line === "\\begin{itemize}") {
            flushParagraph();
            var items = [];
            i += 1;
            while (i < lines.length) {
              var itemLine = lines[i].trim();
              if (itemLine === "\\end{itemize}") break;
              if (itemLine.startsWith("\\item")) {
                items.push(itemLine.replace(/^\\item\s*/, ""));
              }
              i += 1;
            }
            chunks.push(
              "<ul>" +
                items
                  .map(function (item) {
                    return "<li>" + cleanInline(item) + "</li>";
                  })
                  .join("") +
                "</ul>"
            );
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          if (line.startsWith("\\begin{tabular}")) {
            flushParagraph();
            var rows = [];
            i += 1;
            while (i < lines.length) {
              var raw = lines[i].trim();
              if (raw === "\\end{tabular}") break;
              if (!raw || raw === "\\hline") {
                i += 1;
                continue;
              }
              var normalized = raw.replace(/\\\\$/, "").trim();
              var cells = normalized.split("&").map(function (cell) {
                return cell.trim();
              });
              rows.push(cells);
              i += 1;
            }
            chunks.push(renderTable(rows));
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          if (line.startsWith("\\")) {
            i += 1;
            continue;
          }

          paragraph.push(line.replace(/\\\\$/, "").trim());
          i += 1;
        }

        flushParagraph();
        return chunks.join("");
      }

      try {
        if (!root) return;
        root.innerHTML = '<article class="latex-doc">' + renderLatexSubset(source) + "</article>";
      } catch (error) {
        if (root) {
          root.innerHTML = '<p class="latex-loading">Render fallback active. Please refresh the page.</p>';
        }
      }
    })();
  </script>
</BlogLayout>
